    <section id="miracles-main" class="grid-container">
        <div>
            <h1 class="portfolio-title">Miracles</h1>
            <h3 class="portfolio-subtitle">— Typography, 2020 / Adobe Illustrator, After Effects</h3>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="portfolio-section">Objective —</h4>
                    <p class="portfolio-description"><span>To create a gatefold that depicts the short story “Miracles”
                            by Lucy Corin using interesting typography</span>
                        To create a fifteen-second kinetic typography video that depicts a small part of the static
                        gatefold design

                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="portfolio-section">About —</h4>
                    <p class="portfolio-description">Miracles is a story that is told from the perspective of an adult
                        reflecting on her childhood. The story centers on her family and her experience growing up with
                        her father and her brother after her mother left. She uses imagery and descriptions of spiders
                        and a post-apocalyptic setting to draw out further emotions within her story.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h4 class="portfolio-section">Process —</h4>
                    <p class="portfolio-description"><span>(Static) Print: The quotation marks were used to express the
                            spider and/or its footprints, which the author emphasized in the story; the size and the
                            quantity grow bigger as the story progresses. The use of different orientations for father,
                            mother, and brother were intended to reflect the different relationships that the author had
                            with each one of them. Special emphasis was depicted on the placement and repetition of text
                            to show the shifts in mood that occur throughout the story. The last panel is the only panel
                            that is figure-ground reversal because it is filled with confusion and questions that the
                            author has for her brother about their childhood.</span>
                        (Dynamic) Video: Like the static version, there was a desire to include the quotation marks and
                        the odd but carefully placed text. It was important to emphasize both the quiet, subtle aspects
                        and the jagged, bold movements. The video also divides into two: before and after “do you
                        remember”; the sudden background shift from white to black follows the format of the static
                        version, which in the video creates a clearer recollection of her past.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </section>

